Brazil Senator Gleisi Hoffman May Replace Palocci, Estado Says

-- B y   M a t t h e w   B r i s t o w
-- 
2011-06-07T21:41:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-07/brazil-senator-gleisi-hoffman-may-replace-palocci-estado-says.html
Senator Gleisi Hoffmann is the most
likely candidate to replace Brazil’s chief of staff  Antonio Palocci  after he resigned today, O Estado de S.Paulo newspaper
 reported , without saying where it got the information.  Hoffmann met with President Dilma Rousseff this afternoon,
Joao Domingos and Leonencio Nossa said on their blog published
on the newspaper’s website. Palocci resigned today, saying that
accusations against him caused a “political fight” that could
damage his performance as a minister, according to an e-mailed
statement sent by his office.  Hoffman is the wife of Communications Minister  Paulo Bernardo .  To contact the reporters on this story:
Matthew Bristow in Brasilia at 
 mbristow5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net  